# Portfolio Project Rules

## Project Overview
This is a Next.js portfolio website built with TypeScript and Tailwind CSS.
It features a single-page interaction model with section reveals via navigation pills.

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling (no CSS modules)
- Prefer functional components with hooks
- Use "use client" directive only when state/effects are needed
- Keep components small and focused

## File Organization
- Components go in `/components`
- Section components go in `/components/sections`
- Pages go in `/app`
- Static assets go in `/public`

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `NavPill.tsx`)
- Files: PascalCase for components, lowercase for configs
- CSS classes: Tailwind utilities only

## Design System
- Primary gradient: `from-purple-400 to-pink-400`
- Background: `from-purple-100 via-pink-50 to-blue-50`
- Border radius: Large (rounded-2xl, rounded-3xl)
- Shadows: Soft (shadow-lg, shadow-xl)
- Transitions: Subtle, smooth

## Best Practices
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Semantic HTML
- Accessible components (ARIA labels)
- Optimized images
- Minimal client-side JavaScript
- Server components by default
